        {
            "id": 1,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "Identifying parallel web pages from bilingual web sites is a crucial step of bilingual resource construction for cross-lingual information processing . <S>",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "In this paper , we propose a link-based approach ",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "to distinguish parallel web pages from bilingual web sites . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "Compared with the existing methods , ",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "which only employ the internal translation similarity ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "( such as content-based similarity and page structural similarity ) , ",
            "relation": "EXEMPLIFICATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "we hypothesize ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "that the external translation similarity is an effective feature ",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "to identify parallel web pages . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "Within a bilingual web site , web pages are interconnected by hyperlinks . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "The basic idea of our method is that the translation similarity of two pages can be inferred from their neighbor pages , ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "which can be adopted as an important source of external similarity . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "Thus , the translation similarity of page pairs will influence each other . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT-REASON"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "An iterative algorithm is developed ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 14,
            "text": "to estimate the external translation similarity and the final translation similarity . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 16,
            "parent": 14,
            "text": "Both internal and external similarity measures are combined in the iterative algorithm . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 17,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "Experiments on six bilingual websites demonstrate ",
            "relation": "EVALUATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 18,
            "parent": 17,
            "text": "that our method is effective ",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
